<dl id="un5004ba"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un5" href="#un5004">UN5: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un5all.htm#un5004ba"> (NLI.5B) 4(ba)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Mask Tarnkappe <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="un5004ba"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/f/lexf.htm#un5004ba">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/f/f86.htm#un5004ba">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/f/f86.htm#un5004ba">1986 (6.900)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/f/l22f.htm#un5004ba">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#un5004ba">MS PL-3</ms> </li><li>JJA 17:267 </li><li><a name="fd8" href="../udra/u6da.htm#fd8">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/f/fd8.htm#un5004ba">Draft: 6.8</a> </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: Copied from <a name="un3026d" href="un3all.htm#un3026d">UN3 (VIII.A.5):026(d)</a>. See also <a name="un6014at" href="un6all.htm#un6014at">UN6 (NLI.4):014(at)</a>. The most famous Norse &lsquo;magical helmet&rsquo; was called Hildegrim, or Helkappe, or Tarnkappe, the &lsquo;cap of darkness.&rsquo; Wearing it rendered one invisible and able to move in and out of the underworld. Some write that the mask was made of dogskin, and that it was the mask worn by Hades. </mm> </dd></dl>
